\par\par \b \uc2  Global slowdown, SARS still a threat to RI  \highlight22\uc2 economy \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 505 \uc2 words\par \uc2 14 April 2003\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  13 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2003 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Dadan Wijaksana, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  As the war in Iraq comes to a conclusion, one \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  clouding the world \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  has now been lifted. But the prospects for the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  remain gloomy due the threats posed by the flu-like disease, SARS, economists say. \par \par \uc2  StanChart economist Fauzi Ichsan said that although the Iraq war was relatively short, it still had a negative impact on the world \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which in turn would also affect the local \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "We predict that the world \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will now grow by around 3 percent with the war, as compared to around 4 percent without the war. This will obviously have an impact on the domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," Fauzi said. \par \par \uc2  By comparison, the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  posted growth of around 2.8 percent last year. \par \par \uc2  Even without the war, a rebound in the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would still take some time because of the continued slow pace of recovery in the U.S., Fauzi added. \par \par \uc2  The U.S. is one of the world's major \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  dynamos, with around one third of the world's total exports being absorbed by the country. It is also one of Indonesia's main export destinations. \par \par \uc2  A slower recovery in the U.S. would only further slow down the already fragile world \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "Not to mention what will happen if the United Nations (UN) and European Union (EU) are not included in the Iraq reconstruction program. In such a case, the U.S. would have to shoulder the huge financial burden alone. \par \par \uc2  "This would put more pressure on the U.S. \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he said. \par \par \uc2  Analysts have predicted that at least US$100 billion will be needed to rebuild Iraq. \par \par \uc2  Fauzi was commenting on the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  prospects now that the Iraq war is virtually over following the taking of control of Baghdad by U.S. ground forces last week. \par \par \uc2  The three-week war, which was much shorter than anticipated by many, lifted earlier fears of another round of world recession should it have turned out to be prolonged. \par \par \uc2  But, not only had the war already taken its toll on the world \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the recent emergence of Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome (SARS) would also have the potential to further slow down global growth. \par \par \uc2  SARS, which has claimed many lives throughout the world, was damaging the tourism sector worldwide, especially in countries heavily dependent on the service-based \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "But, equally importantly, it further damages investor confidence in the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , including Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which is in dire need of investment," Fauzi said. \par \par \uc2  Another thing that had the potential to damage the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  here was international oil prices. \par \par \uc2  After soaring in the run-up to the war, oil prices have steadily come down, with analysts fearing they could sink below $22 per barrel, the benchmark level set in the 2003 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  If that happens, the government would somehow have to make up the loss in potential revenues generated from oil exports. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2003 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020030414dz4e00013\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  UN Revises the Projection of RI's Growth. \b0\par\par\uc2 494 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 April 2003\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2003 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The United Nations had revised its projection on Indonesian growth of 2003 to 3.4% from its initial growth projection of 4.1%. The revision was due to the outbreak of severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS), Iraq crisis and the falling of international trade. \par \par \uc2  Prabowo, Senior International Trade Strategist of the United Nations Support Facility for Indonesian Recovery (UNSFIR) also predicted that the whole region of Asia Pacific would book a growth of 5%. \par \par \uc2  "It is lower than our initial projection of 5.4%," he said when announcing the conclusion of a study conducted by \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Social Commission for Asia and Pacific (ESCAP) in Jakarta this week. \par \par \uc2  Prabowo was of the opinion that the growth of Asian Pacific countries would depend on the domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  rather than on the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "Therefore intra regional trade will be a more considerable alternative. A country, besides issuing some \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  stimuli, must be more focus to boost its trade with all countries in the region," he said. \par \par \uc2  Prabowo went on saying that China's growth would down from initial projection 0f 7.7% to 7.5%. He said, however, China's growth would be the highest in the region. \par \par \uc2  The study of ESCAP also mentioned that the debt of many Asian Pacific countries including Indonesia would increase to more than 50% of the gross domestic products (GDP) so that it would be more difficult for those countries to issue some \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  stimuli. \par \par \uc2  In this regard ESCAP called for Asian Pacific countries to be more discipline in running its \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to keep the inflation low, the exchange rate stable and the interest rate low. \par \par \uc2  The United Nations also predicted that the export performance of the country would not be better than that in the previous years. So far Indonesian export had down by 2.4% due to the some \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis in Japan, the United States and the European countries. \par \par \uc2  Prabowo went on saying that to boost its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, the country should restore its investment climate. \par \par \uc2  He said that the government already had many program to attract more investors, but it could not execute the program effectively. \par \par \uc2  A consistent \b \highlight22\uc2 economic policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , he said, would be a key to improve the investment climate in Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  "The program of the government should be on track no matter the next government will be," he said. \par \par \uc2  On another occasion the chairman of Indonesian Businessmen Association (Apindo) Harijadi B. Sukamdani said that the government did not adequately respond to the global crisis. \par \par \uc2  "There is a gap between the perception among the society and the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  taken by government," he said in a discussion on \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  after Iraq War in Jakarta this week. \par \par \uc2  In such worst global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition, he said, Indonesian businessmen still had to deal with the price increase of energy and water. \par \par \uc2  "In such \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  global condition, the government actually has to strengthen domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he said. (06). \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020030421dz4j00006\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
