\par\par \b \uc2  `Govt must push local consumption amid global  \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty \highlight\uc2 '. \b0\par\par\uc2 592 \uc2 words\par \uc2 28 April 2003\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  13 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2003 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Dadan Wijaksana, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  With the world's gloomy \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  outlook expected to further hinder the country's performance in exports and attracting investment, the government has no choice but to focus on policies that can boost domestic consumption, experts say. \par \par \uc2  Economist Chatib Basri and businessman Djimanto shared the same view that domestic consumption, which is now showing signs of weakening, could play an increased role in pushing \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, as had happened in the past couple of years. \par \par \uc2  "The government has to turn to domestic market-minded policies under the unfavorable external conditions as in the near future we have to rely on robust consumption to drive the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," Chatib, of the respected Institute for Economics and Social Research, Faculty of \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , University of Indonesia, told The Jakarta Post on Sunday. \par \par \uc2  War in Iraq and the outbreak of Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome (SARS) has dimmed prospects for international \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. \par \par \uc2  It is feared that a fragile global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will further hurt the economies of export-oriented countries like Indonesia, and create jitters among investors. \par \par \uc2  Against this backdrop, boosting domestic consumption should be on top of the government's list of priorities. There are at least two things that can be done by the government to achieve that, Chatib said. \par \par \uc2  On the demand side the government needed to maintain the people's purchasing power and on the supply side it needed to create policies that ensured the prices of goods and services on the domestic market were cheaper. \par \par \uc2  "Maintaining the stability of macroeconomic indicators, such as inflation, will ensure people keep \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as high inflation would otherwise lessen the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 's buying ability," Chatib said. \par \par \uc2  Inflation has been so far kept controllable. Date recorded in the first two months of the year is in line with the government's full-year inflation target of 9 percent, thanks to a relatively stable rupiah against the U.S. dollar. \par \par \uc2  On the supply front, priority should be given to policies that reduce the costs of products and services, which could eventually spur \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Among other things, Chatib said, the government should modify existing \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  laws on luxury goods, seen as detrimental to creating competitive prices. \par \par \uc2  Djimanto, the chairman of Indonesian Employers Association (Apindo), agreed, saying there were policies that could be taken to reduce production costs, thus reducing the prices of goods, which could in turn boost private consumption. \par \par \uc2  Apart from modifying \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  laws, production costs could be significantly reduced by getting rid of various levies and lowering utility prices, including electricity and fuel. \par \par \uc2  However, while admitting robust domestic consumption was crucial in propping up \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities, Djimanto was of the opinion that such incentives, or \b \highlight22\uc2 stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2 , should be given more to local firms that can better compete, in terms of prices, with imported ones. \par \par \uc2  "We surely do not want to see robust domestic consumption driven mainly by the sale of imported products," Djimanto told the Post on Sunday. \par \par \uc2  The government, which is struggling to balance its books, has been pushing hard to generate as much revenue from \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  as possible. \par \par \uc2  In his response, Chatib said: "It's a matter of priority, we know how tight the government's \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  is, meaning that it needs plenty of income, but this has to be done to spur the much-needed \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities." \par \par \uc2  The government has targeted \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth of four percent for this year, but due to SARS and a lingering recession in developed economies, some say the target is unattainable. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2003 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020030428dz4s0000h\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
