\par\par \b \uc2  Govt determined to part with IMF - Hamzah. \b0\par\par\uc2 519 \uc2 words\par \uc2 3 May 2003\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2003 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Fitri Wulandari, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The government is determined not to extend its agreement with the International Monetary Fund (IMF), due to end this year, Vice President Hamzah Haz said on Friday. \par \par \uc2  "The government is determined to end the IMF (agreement). But we have to prepare ourselves for that. It means we have to tap domestic resources," Hamzah said after Friday prayers at Al Falah Mosque, Tangerang, Banten. \par \par \uc2  Hamzah added that if the government wished to extend the agreement, then it would have to be discussed with the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR), as the MPR annual session last year had clearly ordered termination of the IMF program. \par \par \uc2  Hamzah's comment is the first official statement regarding the issue of IMF program termination. \par \par \uc2  The Vice President recognized that ending the IMF program would mean that Indonesia would have to repay about US$6 billion to $7 billion in outstanding debt to the IMF. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia's foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  stood at US$33.6 billion as of the end of April. \par \par \uc2  Hamzah also expressed his confidence that, without the IMF, Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  status and balance of payments would remain safe, provided that the domestic security situation remained stable and exports increased. \par \par \uc2  "The problem in Aceh should be resolved quickly so as not to become a burden. The banking sector should start extending credits to improve the real sector," he was quoted as saying by detik.com Internet news portal. \par \par \uc2  The government plans to launch a military operation in Aceh to quell a separatist movement in the restive, resource-rich province. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, analysts said military operations in Aceh would create new security \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , possibly increasing next year, at the very time the country would be participating in \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  elections and the first-ever, direct presidential election. \par \par \uc2  With such increasing \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , a number of economists have suggested that the government extend the IMF program, at least to maintain creditor confidence in Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  Economist Fauzi Ichsan from Standard Chartered Bank said that once the IMF exited from the country, the international community would question Indonesia's seriousness in carrying out its own structural \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform programs. \par \par \uc2  "At present, international creditors and investors still have the confidence that Indonesia can carry out its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms because the IMF is watching the process," Fauzi told The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2  Economist Pande Radja Silalahi, from the Centre for Strategic and International Studies (CSIS), said he doubted that the government would seriously implement structural \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms once it terminated the IMF program. \par \par \uc2  He argued that even during the IMF's five-year "tutelage", the government had dragged its feet when it came to implementing the structural \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms set out in the government's letter of intent to the IMF. \par \par \uc2  "If the government had been serious in carrying out \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms in the past, we would have 'graduated' from the IMF sooner and not be dragging on like this, a situation that is costing us dear," Pande said. \par \par \uc2  IMF loans to the country are tied to the government's commitment to implementing \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2003 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020030506dz53000bn\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
