\par\par \b \uc2  House warned against delays in appointing new BI governor. \b0\par\par\uc2 628 \uc2 words\par \uc2 8 May 2003\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  2 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2003 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Dadan Wijaksana, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  Bankers warned the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  (DPR) against delaying the appointment of a new \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  governor because it would undermine confidence in the domestic financial market. \par \par \uc2  The Association of State Banks (Himbara) and the Federation of Private Domestic Banks (Perbanas) said that timing would be of great importance to secure market confidence, meaning sooner would be better than later. \par \par \uc2  "It's all about timing. We cannot afford to encounter any further delays, because it would ruin market confidence," Himbara deputy chairman Saifuddien Hasan told a hearing with House Commission IX for financial affairs on Wednesday. Perbanas officials also attended the meeting. \par \par \uc2  The commission is in charge of selecting the governor. \par \par \uc2  The hearing was held as part of efforts to garner as much input as possible from the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the ongoing process to select a person for the top post at the country's highest monetary authority. \par \par \uc2  President Megawati Soekarnoputri has nominated three people for the post. They are former senior officials of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Burhanuddin Abdullah and Cyrillius Harinowo, and deputy governor Miranda Goeltom. The list of names was sent to the House three months ago. \par \par \uc2  The winning candidate will replace incumbent Governor Sjahril Sabirin, whose tenure ends on May 17. Sjahril has been holding the post since 1998, a year before \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  became an independent \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Based on Law No. 23/1999 on \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the President's list of candidates would have to undergo a fit and proper process conducted by House Commission IX. \par \par \uc2  However, despite receiving the list in early February, the fit and proper test has yet to take place, giving rise to the concern that the whole process may not be completed by the time Sjahril's tenure ends, which is in less than two weeks. \par \par \uc2  According to the law, that would lead to the extension of the incumbent officer's term. \par \par \uc2  The delay could well have the potential to shake the confidence of financial market players. There have been many occasions in the past where lawmakers delayed key government \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  programs due to various problems that create \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  But Commission IX chairman Max Muin said that an extension of Sjahril's term would not be necessary as the commission had pledged to finish the selection job before May 17. \par \par \uc2  "I can assure you that we will complete the fit and proper test on the three candidates before May 12, because we've already scheduled a plenary meeting for the next day to report the commission's choice. \par \par \uc2  "So, before May 17, or the day that Sjahril's tenure ends, we will have the name of his successor," Max told the hearing, at which \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's employees association was also present. \par \par \uc2  When each banking association was asked which candidate they hoped would become the next \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  governor, they refused to give a clear answer, saying that based on the market's response, all three candidates were seen as market friendly. \par \par \uc2  Economists have warmly welcomed the nominations, saying that not only are they all regarded as professionals and have a good track record in managing the monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , but none of them are politicians. \par \par \uc2  However, there are reports which suggest that the fight for the top \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  post will likely be between Miranda Goeltom, who is backed by Megawati's Indonesian Democratic Party of Struggle, and Burhanuddin, who is supported by Vice President Hamzah Haz's United Development Party and other smaller Muslim-based political parties. \par \par \uc2  Reports said that the winner would depend on which person would be supported by the Golkar Party, which had unsuccessfully asked Megawati to include other names on the list of candidates. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2003 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020030508dz580005l\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
