\par\par \b \uc2  Banks still reluctant to boost loans, BI says. \b0\par\par\uc2 527 \uc2 words\par \uc2 13 May 2003\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  14 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2003 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Dadan Wijaksana, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  acknowledged on Monday that the country's banking sector had been slow in channeling new loans to the real sector despite a drop in the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  benchmark interest rate. \par \par \uc2  "There are at least three reasons why banks continue to be reluctant in providing loans," \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  deputy governor Miranda Goeltom told reporters on the sidelines of a meeting with legislators. \par \par \uc2  She said the first reason was that investing in the corporate sector were still considered risky as many of the companies had yet to complete their debt restructuring process. \par \par \uc2  "The second one refers to the fact that banks remain reluctant to lend in an environment where investor confidence remains weakened by global \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 ." \par \par \uc2  She said the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  downturn, highlighted by the shaky \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  performance of the world's major \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  powers such as the U.S. and Japan, had further discouraged banks to provide loans to export-oriented firms. \par \par \uc2  "If the U.S. \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  can only grow by around 2 percent each year, banks consider that as a risk to be taken into account before providing loans to exporters," Miranda said. \par \par \uc2  Along with Singapore, the U.S. and Japan are Indonesia's main export destinations. \par \par \uc2  The third reason was the banking industry's traumatic experience in the past, she said. \par \par \uc2  In the past, local banks aggressively channeled their funds to the private sector, often their affiliated businesses, without a sound and proper credit risk assessment. It was the absence of such action that is believed to have contributed to the systematic collapse of the banking industry in 1997-1998. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has been guiding downward the interest rate of the one-month \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  SBI promissory notes in the past year. The SBI rate is currently hovering at 10.91 percent, compared to more than 17 percent early last year. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  expects the lower rate environment will encourage more bank loans to help companies expand their businesses and create more jobs. \par \par \uc2  But the latest data showed that in the first quarter of the year, new loans only stood at a mere Rp 88 billion. Throughout 2002, the total new loans reached Rp 62 trillion. \par \par \uc2  Late last week, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governor Sjahril Sabirin said the current SBI rate was low enough, indicating the rate was unlikely to fall further in the near future. \par \par \uc2  But Miranda, who is running for the governor post, told reporters there was still room for a further cut in the benchmark rate, in hopes to force banks to also further lower its lending rates. \par \par \uc2  "If the current condition keeps improving, the interest rate could fall to around 10.5 percent," she said. \par \par \uc2  Only by a lower lending rate, the private sector would be tempted to turn to banks to seek working capital, she said, which would consequently accelerate productive activities and bode well for the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth. \par \par \uc2  The lending rate currently stands at a range of 17 percent to 18 percent. \par \par \uc2  Benign inflation has been the main reason for \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  to allow its benchmark interest rate go down. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2003 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020030513dz5d0000i\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
