labor market annually, let alone the millions of others who lost their jobs at the height of the crisis in 1998 and 1999.  \par \par \uc2 What fundamentally went wrong?  \par \par \uc2 Analysts and businesspeople blame the persistently low growth on the long bakclog in structural and legal reforms that has kept the environment inimical to new investment, while private consumption, which has been the main locomotive of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  since 2000, has been losing steam due to lack of savings and mounting consumer debts.  \par \par \uc2 Most structural reform has largely been behind schedule due to a combination of strong resistance from vested interest groups within the government, poor leadership within the executive branch, adversary relations between the executive and \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  branches and inadequate institutional capacity to execute reform. - The Jakarta Post.  \par \par \uc2 Editorial: THE RACE AMONG PARTIES  \par \par \uc2 The reform movement has been fighting for its life amid increasing \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 . To certain groups of students, the reform movement has been dead, thus they urge President Megawati Soekarnoputri and Vice President Hamzah Haz to resign for failing to maintain the spirit of reform.  \par \par \uc2 However, amid the lack of reform spirit, a couple of parties have been able to buck the skepticism - the United Development Party (PPP) and Golkar Party.  \par \par \uc2 The two parties have opened themselves to the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  for membership. PPP for instance, has invited those willing to be members of the \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  body representing the Islamic-based party.  \par \par \uc2 Golkar, cornered by certain quarters, has claimed to be the most prapared for reforms by recruiting its presidential nominee through a convention.  \par \par \uc2 Is it wrong for parties not to open themselves to outsiders to be nominated for president? Of course not, as it is an agreement that has to be appreciated. However, both PPP and Golkar have shown the courage to change. One of the reasons why reform is fading away is that the elite group lack the courage to make sacrifices. It is not enough for PPP and Golkar to race in inviting outsiders to presidential nomination, to prove that they are reformists. Old and new parties are faced with the question on the willingness of their leaders to leave their positions in the party once they are elected as \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials. If party leaders are daring enough to do that, they will do a  \par \par \uc2 good turn for this nation's life. - Media Indonesia.   \par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020030523dz5m00036\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 Rupiah Appreciation must Reflect the Market.  \b0\par\par\uc2 624 \uc2 words\par \uc2 22 May 2003\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2003 Bisnis Indonesia  \par \par \uc2 Lin Che Wei, a market analyst, urged the government and \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  to focus on stabilizing rupiah so that the appreciation of the local currency reflecting the real condition of the market.  \par \par \uc2 If the government and \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  did so, he said, the appreciation of local currency would mean the improvement of business confident to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  of Indonesia.  \par \par \uc2 He was of the opinion that stable rupiah would be benefiting for businessmen, while the appreciation of the currency would just ignite the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  of foreign exchange market in the long run.  \par \par \uc2 Lin added that appreciation of rupiah would ignite some volatility and hurt Indonesian exporters.  \par \par \uc2 "I am afraid that the fast appreciation of rupiah will be unstable. It will place Indonesian exporters in danger as actually they need some steady guidance," he said yesterday.  \par \par \uc2 According to Lin, there should be an X factor behind the appreciation of rupiah because US dollar was also appreciating.  \par \par \uc2 He was of the opinion that rupiah was strengthening as there was some inflow of dollar to invest in the domestic capital market. Regarding this he urged the government and \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  to aware as this kind of investment would not be permanent.  \par \par \uc2 "Our \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was stable, but it is better for rupiah not to strengthen quickly. Maybe the appreciation of rupiah was due to the capital inflow, but it will be dangerous," he said.  \par \par \uc2 He said that the capital inflow would be positive for the country if it built a capital formation so that it would be able to utilize the idle capacity of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .  \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery had been close, he said, since the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  had started to be active while domestic condition was also improving.  \par \par \uc2 Such situation, he said, was supposed to drive Indonesian export. But in fact the improving rupiah had been boosting domestic consumption.  \par \par \uc2 Cyrillus Harinowo of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  said that in the post IMF era Indonesia should be able to attract foreign capital and improve banking sector so that it would improve the domestic real sector.  \par \par \uc2 "The problem is that it is difficult to improve the domestic purchasing power," he said.  \par \par \uc2 Aceh Factor  \par \par \uc2 Meanwhile the President Director of Bank Buana Pardi Kendy touch the level of IDR8,400 per US$ two days ago due to the negative sentiment about Aceh.  \par \par \uc2 "Speculators keep trying to bring rupiah to around IDR8