\par\par \b \uc2  Planned bill to secure Bappenas' legal authority. \b0\par\par\uc2 454 \uc2 words\par \uc2 29 May 2003\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  13 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2003 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Dadan Wijaksana, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The National Development Planning Board (Bappenas) plans to draft a bill on \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development that will allow it to retain its role in drawing up the country's short and medium-term development programs, including the annual state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The plan was divulged by State Minister for National Development Planning/Bappenas chairman Kwik Kian Gie on Wednesday, during a meeting with \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  Commission IX for state financial affairs. \par \par \uc2  Legislators voiced support for the plan, saying the bill, when passed into law, would provide a strong legal basis for the continued existence of Bappenas. \par \par \uc2  "We agree on the importance of a stronger legal basis, in the form of a law, for the national development planning system," the chairman of Commission IX, Max Moein, said following the hearing with Bappenas. \par \par \uc2  The recent enactment of the state finance law created \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the fate of Bappenas. According to this new law, Bappenas would no longer play an active role in drawing up the government's annual state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , with the finance ministry taking complete control over drafting the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The state finance law also stipulates that Propenas, a five-year development program prepared by Bappenas, which in the past has been used as the main reference point for drafting the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , is no longer suitable or realistic within today's fast-changing \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  framework. \par \par \uc2  According to the state finance law, the Propenas would be replaced by a document called the Medium-Term \b \highlight22\uc2 Expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2  Framework (MTEF), which would be an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  guide for a three-year period. \par \par \uc2  This raised speculation that the once-powerful Bappenas would either be dissolved or its role drastically shrunk. \par \par \uc2  The state finance law was drafted by the finance ministry and was approved by a special House committee, which included a number of Commission IX lawmakers. \par \par \uc2  Sources say President Megawati Soekarnoputri did not sign the law, but it has nevertheless come into effect because it has been over a month since it was approved by the House. \par \par \uc2  Kwik refused to provide details of the planned law on national \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development planning, saying that everything was still being assessed. \par \par \uc2  During the hearing, however, while all of the legislators supported a continued role for Bappenas, a few of the lawmakers questioned how the agency could best be utilized in the future. \par \par \uc2  One legislator suggested that Bappenas would be much more beneficial if it became independent instead of being part of the government structure. \par \par \uc2  Bappenas, established 40 years ago, in the past, particularly during the administration of president Soeharto, was a very powerful agency as all key projects had to pass through the office for approval. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2003 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020030528dz5t0000n\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
