\par\par \b \uc2  Exit strategy from IMF must not create  \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty \highlight\uc2  - BI. \b0\par\par\uc2 587 \uc2 words\par \uc2 24 June 2003\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  13 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2003 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  Dadan Wijaksana, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  warned on Monday the government's exit strategy from the International Monetary Fund (IMF) must not create \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as it would come at the expense of confidence in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  - which has been on the rise lately. \par \par \uc2  Hartadi Sarwono, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's newly inaugurated deputy governor, therefore suggested that the government, in repaying its debts to the IMF, stick with the initial repayment schedule whatever exit strategy was adopted after the current program expires later this year. \par \par \uc2  "The maturity profile of the debts (to the IMF) has been set clearly. Why don't we follow it? Don't ask for a revision, it would only create further \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," Hartadi told reporters on the sidelines of the swearing-in ceremony. \par \par \uc2  By not creating new \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the rising confidence in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as seen in the country's current stable macroeconomic indicators, could then be maintained, he explained. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia is currently on the verge of ending a five-year US$5 billion IMF loan program, which was first established in 1999, and a special team is now exploring the best possible options for the post-program relationship with the IMF. \par \par \uc2  In return for the financial aid, the IMF set out conditions in a number of letters of intent (LoI), which contained the country's key \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform programs and several time-bound targets, which the government has to meet quarterly. \par \par \uc2  After the IMF program ends, Indonesia will owe about $9 billion in total debts to the Fund. The country needs to return at least some $6 billion as its quota as an IMF member only stands at less than $3 billion. \par \par \uc2  However, it remains undecided whether the payments of the excess funds will be made altogether, or follow the initial schedule, which runs until 2010. \par \par \uc2  Currently, the country's international foreign \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which will be used to repay the debts, stand at around $34 billion. \par \par \uc2  State Minister for National Development Planning Kwik Kian Gie is among those who have suggested that Indonesia should immediately repay all its debts to the IMF so that the Fund could no longer exert influence over the management of the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  affairs. \par \par \uc2  Others, however, say that Indonesia must use its \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  wisely to further boost confidence, and therefore there is no need to repay the IMF loans - which carry low \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  - all at once. \par \par \uc2  Separately, Minister of Finance Boediono said that a careful and thorough analysis had to be done in selecting an exit strategy from the IMF as a wrong decision could have a serious impact on the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political circumstances. \par \par \uc2  Boediono pointed out that there were three crucial things the government needed to do to continue the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery program in the post IMF era, which all had a lot to do with retaining confidence in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  They were: ensuring \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  sustainability in the 2004 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the success of 2004 general election process and maintaining national integrity by allocating sufficient funds to the regions through the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Due to its critical nature, Boediono described the transition to a post-IMF world as a "critical juncture" in the country's efforts to build continued confidence in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "This confidence is very important. We need to show that the government is capable of taking care of its own finances and that we're also capable of consistently undertaking \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform," he said. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2003 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020030624dz6o0006b\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
