\par\par \b \uc2  `Macroeconomic gains yet to boost growth'. \b0\par\par\uc2 505 \uc2 words\par \uc2 14 July 2003\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2003 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  The Jakarta Post, Batu, Malang \par \par \uc2  The current strengthening of the country's macroeconomic indicators has yet to be converted into robust growth in the real sector of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  due to lingering problems in other areas, Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Dorodjatun Kuntjoro-Jakti said on Sunday. \par \par \uc2  He said that to help turn around the situation, the business climate at home must be improved through the acceleration of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform. \par \par \uc2  Dorodjatun was speaking at the opening of the 15th annual congress of the high-profile Indonesian Economists Association (ISEI). \par \par \uc2  Since the beginning of the year, the rupiah has been rapidly appreciating against the U.S. dollar, largely due to the weakening of the greenback against major currencies. The strengthening of the local unit has greatly contributed to the current benign inflation environment. This situation has allowed the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to continue cut down its benchmark interest rate. \par \par \uc2  Dorodjatun acknowledged that the increasingly stable macroeconomic picture has created a virtuous circle within the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  as the stronger local unit has attracted a bigger flow of portfolio capital, which facilitates the government's privatization and asset divestment programs. \par \par \uc2  He added the declining trend in the \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  interest rate has reduced the government's burden in servicing its huge domestic debts. \par \par \uc2  But private sector investment still lags behind due to various \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , he said. \par \par \uc2  Dorodjatun explained that to help remedy the problem, the government was determined to press ahead with reform programs aimed at boosting the investment climate and reinvigorating the real sector. \par \par \uc2  He said that one of the programs were to push banks to allocate a greater amount of credit to the small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs). \par \par \uc2  He said that for 2003, the amount of the bank loans to the SMEs sector was estimated to have increased to Rp 42 trillion, compared to around Rp 32 trillion allocated last year. \par \par \uc2  Another effort was to revive the development of key infrastructure projects which were stalled in the wake of the late 1990s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis, Dorodjatun said. \par \par \uc2  President Megawati Soekarnoputri last week relaunched dozens of the stalled projects. \par \par \uc2  Dorodjatun said that another area of reform was boosting institutional capacity. "This is an ongoing process," he said, pointing out as an example that improving the legal system could not be done overnight. \par \par \uc2  He added that currently there were around 50 bills relating to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and investment sector awaiting to be approved by the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of\b0 \highlight\b \highlight22\uc2 Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 . If the bills were approved, legal certainty in the country would "be much better". \par \par \uc2  ISEI chairman Bambang Sudibyo had similar view, saying that the poor investment climate at home prompted foreign investors to put a risk premium on Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  He said that the current ISEI meeting would be closely followed by the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  as the economists grouping was expected to come up with ideas on how to resolve the pressing problems of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  particularly as the country was about to end its current program with the International Monetary Fund. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 2003 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020030714dz7e0000p\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
