\par\par \b \uc2  Govt insists on maintaining high forex level. \b0\par\par\uc2 479 \uc2 words\par \uc2 9 August 2003\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  13 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2003 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \par \uc2  The Minister of Finance, Boediono, said on Friday that the government would stick with its original plan to repay the International Monetary Fund loan in seven years, turning down a suggestion from the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of\b0 \highlight\b \highlight22\uc2 Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 , that the government should take advantage of the country's relatively high foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  to complete the plan in three years. \par \par \uc2  Boediono said that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would still need to maintain high forex \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  amid lingering \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , particularly in 2004, when the country holds general elections. \par \par \uc2  "2004 will be a crucial year filled with many \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , politics, and security. So we must be ready with sufficient forex \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he told reporters. \par \par \uc2  The Chairman of the House \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  Committee, Abdullah Zainie, was quoted by Kompas daily as saying that, the House recommended that the government cut the country's debt to the IMF to below the member quota level of around $3 billion by 2006 - so that the Fund could no longer influence the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies. Under the House proposal, the government would have to allocate more than US$2 billion each year for installments. The country's debt to the IMF would, therefore, reach $9.8 billion when the existing IMF bailout program ends this year. \par \par \uc2  Under the government's repayment plan, annual installments would be less than $1 billion, with the aim of decreasing the debt to below the quota level by 2010. \par \par \uc2  The government will not extend the current IMF program when it expires at the end of this year, but has decided to maintain the Fund's monitoring role via the post program monitoring arrangement (PPM), under which the government must discuss its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies with the Fund. \par \par \uc2  President Megawati Soekarnoputri is expected to unveil the country's post-IMF \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform policies on Aug. 15 with the 2004 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Some experts have said that the termination of the IMF program would expose the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to various risks, largely the absence of a debt rescheduling facility (from the Paris Club of creditor nations). This would cause a serious \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  threat unless the government found alternative funding sources. One alternative is for the government to tap the overseas financial market by issuing bonds. \par \par \uc2  Analysts have said that it is crucial for the government to maintain investors confidence by pushing ahead with tough \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform programs. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  senior deputy governor Anwar Nasution also said that it would be wiser for the government to maintain a high forex reserve level, to deal with the various \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  caused by the threat of terrorism and the general election. \par \par \uc2  "We should stick with the (original) plan," he was quoted by Antara as saying. \par \par \uc2  "The House must not interfere in \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  affairs by 