\par\par \b \uc2 KPEN proposes list of must-do actions to govt.   \b0\par\par\uc2 450 \uc2 words\par \uc2 14 August 2003\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 13\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2003 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \par \uc2 The National \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Recovery Committee (KPEN), an influential business lobby, has recently sent to the government a list of actions the latter must do to speed up the pace of the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery.   \par \par \uc2 The proposed actions are basically aimed at improving the investment and business climate at home, which in turn should help push \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth.   \par \par \uc2 "The priorities in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery agenda are maintaining macroeconomic stability, reducing business \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  and risks, as well as improving the investment climate," said the KPEN letter, which was signed by its chairman Sofyan Wanandi. This paper obtained the copy of the letter on Wednesday.   \par \par \uc2 It added that the business community was hopeful that the government could take the recommendations into consideration in drawing-up the country's post-IMF \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform program to be unveiled by President Megawati Soekarnoputri on Friday.   \par \par \uc2 KPEN said a revival of the banking sector's intermediary role was crucial to allow the corporate sector to benefit from the current stability in macroeconomic indicators.   \par \par \uc2 One way to do that was to push \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  on bank loans down to between 12 percent and 15 percent, so that the loans would become more affordable to the business sector.   \par \par \uc2 The macroeconomic picture has been relatively stable since early this year as evident in the rapid appreciation of the rupiah and benign inflation, but this positive development has failed to translate into higher investment activities due to a number of lingering problems and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 As for ways to reduce \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  and risks for the business sector, KPEN urged the government to accelerate the legal reform program, cut red tape, eliminate illegal fees imposed on businesses, improve security conditions, improve implementation of regional autonomy, and resolve labor conflicts.   \par \par \uc2 Those factors have created the high-cost \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and further eroded the country's business climate with investors and businesspeople not receiving any incentives and even being discouraged to do business here, the KPEN letter said.   \par \par \uc2 Another important factor that can help improve the investment and business climate is the reform of the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2  system.   \par \par \uc2 KPEN has also urged the government to provide \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  amnesty to encourage people to start paying their \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  in full.   \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  amnesty could serve as a motivation for \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 -payers to report all their assets, which could in turn boost state \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue, KPEN added. "This can be done by introducing a one-shot \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  amnesty for assets collected until 2002."   \par \par \uc2 KPEN also stressed the importance of providing sufficient business infrastructure and to support \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities, while also highlighting the alarming level of smuggling activities in the country.   \par \par \uc2 Copyright 2003 The Jakarta Post.    \par \par \