\par\par \b \uc2 Govt to shoulder higher fuel  \highlight22\uc2 subsidy \highlight\uc2  in 2003  \highlight22\uc2 budget \highlight\uc2 .   \b0\par\par\uc2 447 \uc2 words\par \uc2 14 August 2003\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 13\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2003 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \par \uc2 The government would have to allocate a much greater amount of money to cover the fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  this year because of higher prices of oil in the international market, says a senior government official.   \par \par \uc2 This could threaten the 2003 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  target.   \par \par \uc2 Director General of Oil and Gas at the Ministry of Energy and Mineral Resources Iin Arifin Takhyan said on Wednesday that expenses for the fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  this year would double to around Rp 25.6 trillion (US$3.08 billion) compared to Rp 13 trillion allocated under the current \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 Iin said the government only had the capacity to cover up to Rp 20 trillion.   \par \par \uc2 "This means that we'll have a higher \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he told reporters.   \par \par \uc2 The government initially planned to further eliminate the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  on various fuel products early this year. The Rp 13 trillion fund was meant only to cover the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  for kerosene, a fuel used mainly by low-income families for cooking.   \par \par \uc2 But widespread protests from the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  in January, forced the government to delay the cut in the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 The current state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumed an average oil price of $22 per barrel, but because of various \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the global market including the recent war in Iraq, the oil price in the international market during the first half of the year was much higher at an average level of $26.15 per barrel. According to one estimate, the average oil price in the second semester would average $24 per barrel. By maintaining the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and because of the higher international oil price, the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  would consequently have to cover a higher \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 Officials from the Ministry of Finance could not be reached to confirm whether the 2003 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  would suffer a higher \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  than the planned 1.8 percent of gross domestic product.   \par \par \uc2 Minister of Finance Boediono has been trying hard to limit the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  in a bid to help create a healthy \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition, a necessary factor to help speed up the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery.   \par \par \uc2 Boediono has targeted this year's \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  to be contained at below 1.8 percent of GDP, so that next year's \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  could be further cut to around 1 percent of GDP.   \par \par \uc2 There is a possibility that the \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  would not deviate much from the targeted figure considering that the rapid appreciation of the rupiah and lower \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  interest rate would reduce the government's expenses in servicing domestic and overseas debts. In addition, the higher international oil prices should also provide the government with higher oil revenue.   \par \par \uc2 Copyright 2003 The Jakarta Post.    \par \par \u