ial development.  \par \par \uc2 "If elected president, I will be ready to carry out the strategy," said Akbar who is also the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  (DPR) speaker.  \par \par \uc2 Akbar last July 30, 2003, decided to fill out a registration form to participate in the party's national convention to elect Golkar's presidential candidate.   \par \par \uc2 \f2 \par  \par     His step had ended earlier \f28 \b \highlight22\uc2 \f2 public uncertainty\f28 \b0 \highlight\uc2 \f2  about whether or\par not he would take part in the convention.\par     On the same day that Akbar took the first step to run in the\par   \f28 \par \par \uc2 \f2 convention, noted Muslim intellectual Nurcholish Madjid withdrew his name from Golkar's list of prospective presidential nominees.  \f28 \par \par \uc2 \f2 Akbar came to Banjarmasin togthert with a few other presidential aspirants in Golkar, namely former population affairs minister Haryono Suyono, former Indonesian military chief H Wiranto   \f28 \par \par \uc2 \f2 \par  \par and legislator Marwah Daud     Ibrahim, who took turns to address\par the gathering.\par     On the occasion, Marwah Daud spoke about the reasons  why she\par would take part in Golkar's convention.\par     One reason, she said, was that the Golkar Party should be\par awakened to bring back the state assets the present government had\par sold.\par      Wiranto who is also a former coordinating minister for\par political and security affairs, underscored the importance of\par national reconciliation for the sake of  national integrity.\par      Haryono Suyono, who is also former chairman of the National\par Family Planning Coordination Agency, remarked   democracy could not\par be developed by blaming each other but by enabling everyone to\par convey his or her ideas on efforts to develop the nation.\par     About the election of national leaders, Haryono, a former\par coordinating minister for people's welfare, said it should not be\par done through any political deal or 'horse trading.'\par     Under the rules of Golkar's convention, presidential aspirants\par   \f28 \par \par \uc2 \f2 must visit different areas in the country to familiarize the people with their respective visions, missions and ideas on Indonesia's development in the future.   \f28 \par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020030910dz9900010\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
