\par\par \b \uc2 Don't expect business as usual next year - Boediono.   \b0\par\par\uc2 501 \uc2 words\par \uc2 13 September 2003\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 2\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2003 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Rendi A. Witular, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \par \uc2 Minister of Finance Boediono warned bankers on Friday to remain prudent as the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would continue to face \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  next year.   \par \par \uc2 Boediono explained that the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  escalated because of possible political tension during the general election year and at a time when the International Monetary Fund (IMF) would no longer take an active role in designing the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  programs.   \par \par \uc2 "Don't expect business as usual this year and next year because we are still in a phase of political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  transition. The country's condition will remain vigilant," he said.   \par \par \uc2 Boediono made the statement during the 15th congress of the Federation of Private Domestic Banks (Perbanas). Perbanas currently has 79 member private banks. Before the late 1990s financial crisis, members totaled 166 banks.   \par \par \uc2 The minister said the government had outlined several strategies to help the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  survive the perilous period mainly by maintaining macroeconomic and \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  stability.   \par \par \uc2 "The most important thing during the transition is that we have to maintain a stable macroeconomic condition. Without it the micro, or the real sector, which currently under performs, can further plunge," he said.   \par \par \uc2 He added that as this would be the main \b \highlight22\uc2 economic policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  focus, the government would not provide any \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  package for the business sector.   \par \par \uc2 "There will be no \b \highlight22\uc2 stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  for the micro sector next year because our \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition is still inadequate for that. I know that our \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is conservative, but we need to be very careful," he said.   \par \par \uc2 The government has implemented belt-tightening measures to establish \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  stability following the financial crisis with the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  this year expected to reach 2 percent of gross domestic product (GDP). The \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  was about 3.7 percent of GDP three years ago. Next year, the \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  is projected to decline to 1.2 percent of GDP.   \par \par \uc2 Over the past couple of years, the government has managed to stabilize macroeconomic indicators. Inflation has declined markedly and the government now expects it will be in the range of 5 percent to 6 percent by year-end.   \par \par \uc2 The government also managed to stabilize the rupiah at around Rp 8,500-Rp 8,600 against the U.S. dollar.   \par \par \uc2 During the banking congress, Boediono also said the absence of IMF programs next year would become a challenge, especially in gaining confidence from investors.   \par \par \uc2 "The IMF's letter of intent has been considered by investors and business people as the benchmark. Thus, we are now preparing a new benchmark called the white paper," said Boediono, referring to a document containing the government's post-IMF \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  programs.   \par \par \uc2 He expected the white paper document to be published in the middle of this month.   \par \par \uc2 Boediono urged banks to monitor the implementation of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  programs set under the white paper document.   \par \par \uc2 The Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry (Kadin) has set up a special unit to do the monitoring role.   \par \par \uc2 Copyright 2003 The Jakarta Post.    \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020030912dz9d00001\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
