\par\par \b \uc2 After Moody's, S&P ups Indonesia's sovereign ratings   \b0\par\par\uc2 The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \uc2 555 \uc2 words\par \uc2 9 October 2003\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 3\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2003 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Standard and Poor's (S&P) Ratings Services upgraded on Wednesday the country's sovereign ratings for the second time this year in the latest vote of confidence in the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  stability.   \par \par \uc2 S&P raised its long-term foreign and local currency ratings on Indonesia by one notch to 'B' from 'B-' and to 'B+' from 'B', respectively. The short-term foreign currency rating was also raised one notch to 'B', the same level as the short-term local currency rating.   \par \par \uc2 While stating that Indonesia needs to further cut its \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  in coming years from an estimated 1.8 percent of gross domestic product (GDP) this year, the agency acknowledged that progress has been made in the past years.   \par \par \uc2 The state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 's \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  has been on a decline over the past three years. After posting a \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  of about 3.7 percent of GDP in 2001, the country pushed down the \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  to 2.5 percent of GDP last year, as part of a commitment to creating \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  consolidation.   \par \par \uc2 Indonesia is also still suffering from a heavy debt burden, although from time to time it has also shown continued signs of declining, the agency said.   \par \par \uc2 The debt-to-GDP ratio is expected to go down to 77 percent by the end of the year, from close to a 100 percent in 2000.   \par \par \uc2 The S&P upgrade came a week after Moody's Investors Services -- another respected global rating agency -- also upgraded the country's ratings on the back of a stronger external financial footing and falling debts.   \par \par \uc2 The country's stronger international \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  should mean that it should have what it takes to retain investor confidence without the presence of the International Monetary Fund (IMF)'s special program, S&P said.   \par \par \uc2 Indonesia \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  stand at about US$$33 billion, something that should also reduce the country's vulnerability to external shocks.   \par \par \uc2 The IMF's special program runs out by year-end with the government saying it would not ask for an extension.   \par \par \uc2 The rupiah and stock market were helped by the sentiment arising from the upgrade.   \par \par \uc2 The rupiah ended the trading at 8,365 per dollar, slightly stronger than 8,395 the day before, with dealers attributing the S&P upgrade as among the reasons.   \par \par \uc2 It was pretty much the same with the Jakarta stock market, where trading closed higher at 624.33, up 1.5 percent from Tuesday's close on the positive sentiment arising from the S&P news.   \par \par \uc2 Still, while painting the outlook for the new ratings as stable, S&P also warned the government of the possible impact of the political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  as the country is now gearing up for general elections next year.   \par \par \uc2 "The ratings on the Republic of Indonesia are constrained by political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," S&P said in a statement.   \par \par \uc2 Traditionally, concerns are high during elections as it has the potential to create instability, as political tensions heighten.   \par \par \uc2 But, "further improvement in the government's \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  position, together with the progress in structural reform, such as judicial and governance reform and a relatively smooth electoral process, Indonesia's creditworthiness could improve faster than most of its peers," it added.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020031010dza90000b\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
