\par\par \b \uc2 Purnomo insists fuel  \highlight22\uc2 subsidy \highlight\uc2  must be maintained   \b0\par\par\uc2 Fitri Wulandari, The Jakarta Post , Jakarta   \par \uc2 539 \uc2 words\par \uc2 28 October 2003\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 13\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2003 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Minister of Energy and Mineral Resources Purnomo Yusgiantoro said government the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  on various fuel products should be maintained through 2004, which is an election year.   \par \par \uc2 "Earlier this year we tried to increase fuel prices but there was a fierce rejection from the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 "There is no way we can scrap the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  (for fuel products) by 2004," Purnomo said.   \par \par \uc2 He said this meant that Law No. 25/2000 on the 2000-2004 National Development Program, which says that \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  on all fuel products except kerosene must be scrapped by 2004, should be revised.   \par \par \uc2 The government has been under pressure from international donors to end the cost fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  to put state finances in order following the devastating impact of the late 1990s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis. Some analysts have also said the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  were largely enjoyed by richer people and encouraged the smuggling of fuel products to neighboring countries.   \par \par \uc2 But ending the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  is a politically difficult task, particularly next year when the country holds its first ever direct election.   \par \par \uc2 Earlier this year, a decision to start cutting the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  and forcing domestic fuel prices to appreciate in tandem with international prices had to be canceled following \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  protests.   \par \par \uc2 The government has allocated Rp 13.2 trillion in the current state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  for fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 . This was initially meant only to cover the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  for kerosene, a fuel product used mainly by low-income families for cooking.   \par \par \uc2 The Ministry of Finance, which is currently discussing the government's 2004 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  draft with the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 , has yet to respond to Purnomo's statement. It would undoubtedly be difficult for Minister of Finance Boediono to accommodate the demand, as it would create an additional burden on the already tight state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , particularly amid rising international oil prices.   \par \par \uc2 Purnomo said that although rising international oil prices would force the government to spend more to maintain current fuel prices, the government would in turn enjoy huge windfall profits from the sale of oil to cover the ballooning \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Indonesia is an oil exporting country.   \par \par \uc2 Oil prices have averaged US$32 per barrel for the past few days, although this price has begun to inch back down to $28 per barrel.   \par \par \uc2 The current state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumed an average oil price of $22 per barrel, but because of various \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the global market, including the recent war in Iraq, oil prices in the international market during the first half of the year averaged $26.15 per barrel.   \par \par \uc2 Legislators and the Ministry of Finance will jointly decide on the size of the fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  for next year based on developments in international oil prices, the currency exchange rate and domestic consumption volume.   \par \par \uc2 They initially set an oil price assumption of $22 per barrel amid a gloomy outlook for global oil prices next year due to fears of oversupply as oil from Iraq enters the market. Additionally, Russia has said it will increase oil production.   \par \par \uc2 At Monday's hearing between the Ministry of Finance and the House \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  committee, the ministry proposed a domestic fuel consumption figure of 61.4 million kiloliters, lower than the initial proposal of 63 million kiloliters.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020031027dzas00013\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
