\par\par \b \uc2 Consumers push  \highlight22\uc2 economy \highlight\uc2  higher   \b0\par\par\uc2 The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \uc2 529 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 November 2003\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 13\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2003 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 The Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  grew faster at 3.93 percent in the third quarter of this year compared to the same period last year, driven mainly by consumer and government \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the Central Statistics Agency (BPS) reported on Monday.   \par \par \uc2 The agency is optimistic that the government's full-year growth target of 4 percent can be achieved.   \par \par \uc2 "I think it (the growth target) can be achieved. \b \highlight22\uc2 Spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  both by the government and the private (sector) is usually higher in the fourth quarter with the Idul Fitri and Christmas celebrations .... There's even a possibility that growth can be more than 4 percent," BPS deputy chairman La Ode Saifuddin told reporters.   \par \par \uc2 BPS said that compared to the second quarter of this year, gross domestic product (GDP), or the value of all goods and services produced in an \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , grew by 2.93 percent in the third quarter if compared to the second quarter. GDP expanded by 1.66 percent in the second quarter from the first quarter.   \par \par \uc2 The agency said that consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  continued to be a significant contributor to the third quarter growth as it grew by 4.80 percent from the same quarter last year.   \par \par \uc2 Analysts have said that aggressive moves by the country's banking sector provide consumer loans have contributed to the strong consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 . This has been made possible as the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has aggressively cut down its benchmark interest rate amid a benign inflation environment, thanks mainly to a stronger exchange rate of the rupiah against the U.S. dollar.   \par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, BPS said that government \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  also contributed significantly as it increased by 9.64 percent. The government usually spends more on various projects and programs during the second half of the year.   \par \par \uc2 But investment and exports remained weak, BPS said.   \par \par \uc2 Investment only grew by 0.03 percent as investors, particularly foreign investors, have been reluctant to resume new investments in the country due to a host of problems such as legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , terrorism threats, poor infrastructure, massive corruption and lingering labor problems. Meanwhile, domestic corporate sector could not make new investments as the banking sector was still afraid to lend fresh money due to the slow progress in the restructuring of the corporate sector's debts.   \par \par \uc2 Analysts have said the poor performance of the export and investment sectors meant the country was unable to achieve its potential \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth of 6-7 percent, a level which analysts said was necessary in order to be able to create enough jobs for the millions of unemployed people and resolve the poverty problem.   \par \par \uc2 Elsewhere, BPS said that almost all sectors in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  were expanding during the third quarter.   \par \par \uc2 The agriculture, plantation, fishery, and forestry sector grew by 0.79 percent; mining (7.43 percent); manufacturing industry (2.36 percent); electricity, gas and clean water (6.71 percent); construction (6.17 percent); trade, hotel and restaurant (3.80 percent); transportation and communications (10.99 percent); finance and leasing (4.89 percent) and services (2.50 percent).   \par \par \uc2 BPS said the size of the country's GDP in the nine-month period of this year totaled Rp 1,291.6 trillion.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020031117dzbi00011\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
